                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15007684" author="sershe" created="Tue, 17 Nov 2015 00:26:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch is on top of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-12341&quot; title=&quot;LLAP: add security to daemon protocol endpoint (excluding shuffle)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HIVE-12341&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HIVE-12341&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. The default option is to use the daemon keytab. In the setup with HTTP user, the keytab and other settings can be set in daemon config (filters, auth type, principal and keytab are the necessary minimum).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15009726" author="sershe" created="Tue, 17 Nov 2015 22:31:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Update: SPNEGO calls are RM-specific and not necessary. One can either directly set the hadoop configs to enable authorization on the web app, or set the new config this patch adds.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15047604" author="sseth" created="Tue, 8 Dec 2015 22:33:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1. A follow up jira would be required to support ACLs, and potentially limiting data on the UI if any query specific information shows up.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15049707" author="sershe" created="Thu, 10 Dec 2015 00:18:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Rebased the patch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
